 According to the weather website, AccuWeather, thunderstorms should hit the Lowveld tomorrow. TRAC N4 said that poor visibility can cause dangerous driving conditions. Road users are reminded to switch head lights on, increase following distance and reduce travelling speed during adverse weather conditions. ALSO READ: Severe weather watch issued for Mpumalanga The released the following tips for driving: Do: • Reduce speed and obey speed limits.
• Switch headlights on.
• Keep following distance.
• Remain patient and considerate. Don’t: • Attempt to pass the vehicle in front of you when visibility is poor.
